intro_home:
    clear_dialog
    run transition intro_home
    add_stat actions -2
    "Sparse decor hangs from the walls, but it means nothing to you."
    "<span class='writtenText'>'Live Laugh Love'</span> tat, tacky pre-war candle holders, dusty vases... you wouldn't have bought any of this crap, surely?"
    clear_dialog
    "Cardboard boxes are scattered about containing possessions that you can only assume you cherish. Either you have not lived here for long, or you have some serious issues with your executive function."
    if (roll intro_home_function_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "Both."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    play sound footstepsinside
    //run transition intro_study_blood
    run transition_study true
    "Your empty wanderings leave you yearning for a return to the womb, and so you head back upstairs into the bedroom."
    clear_dialog
    "It's spitting outside now, rainwater pools on the wooden floor, but in the absence of any emotional connection to the abode there is no sense of urgency in fixing it. There is blood on the wall, yours, presumably. Orb made quite an impact."
    "Your fur is clean, though, which is comforting. It seems Orb did an okay job at patching you back up."
    clear_dialog
    "The bedroom has been less fortunate. Shards of Qing china, splintered wood and shreds of singed insulation carpet the floor."
    clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "We should clean this place up, Ghost. Maybe it'll help jog your memory, maybe not."
    talk orb talk "Either way I think it'll be a good way to make sure your delicate, bony little body is still functioning properly, despite me being embedded in it."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk orb talk "How are you feeling by the way? Any better?"
        "Okay I guess. I think I might have IBS though.":
            talk orb talk "You'll be fine. Probably. Just power through it till you're feeling better, that's the Anglian spirit, right?"
            talk lovely talk "To be Anglian is to bear all the weight of creation. You're correct, Orb."
            talk nasty talk "Pip pip what ho, innit."
            jump intro_home_menu

intro_home_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The cottage creaks. It is in pain, as you are. Perhaps giving it a tidy will make it feel better?"
        "[Dust the debris off of the floor before your feet get any splinters]" if (!= $data.intro.debris true):
            jump intro_home_debris
        roll intro_home_menu_blood_nasty nasty 80 "[Lick the wallpaper until the blood comes out]" hideAfterRoll:
            success "":
                set data.intro.blood true
                set data.intro.bloodCleaned true
                run transition_fromStudy intro_blood_lick
                "It's tough work, but someone's got to do it. Your reward is the unforgettable taste of wallpaper paste, wallpaper, wall and blood. It was worth it, you think."
                clear_dialog
                talk nasty talk "Hey, nice one Ghost. Getting blood out of wallpaper isn't an easy task without special chemicals, but I think we did the job pretty well."
                talk orb talk "I'll admit I'm impressed. I kept thinking of butting in to explain why licking the bloodstain was not your best option, but I know when to admit I'm wrong."
                talk lovely talk "I shan't be admitting anything! That was positively ghastly!"
                // run transition intro_study
                run transition_study true
                jump intro_home_menu
            failed ""
                set data.intro.blood true
                run transition_fromStudy intro_blood_lick
                "It won't come out, no matter how hard you lick. The blood just stays there, taunting you."
                "In fact you seem to have actively made things *worse*, for your wall no longer bares the dramatic flair of a bloodstain, but the gross unpleasantness of a bloodsmudge."
                clear_dialog
                "You may also have rubbed all of your tastebuds off. You give the wall a final lick to check. It tastes of wallpaper."
                "That's good. Your tongue is safe, for now."
                clear_dialog
                talk orb talk "*Who* would have thought licking a bloodstain would not clean it. We're learning a lot today, aren't we?"
                talk nasty talk "Weird right? Usually a bit of deft tongue work can get you anything."
                clear_dialog
                // run transition intro_study_blood
                run transition_study true
                jump intro_home_menu
        "[Pick up the broken vase before you step on a shard and presumably die horribly from the resulting infection]" if (!= $data.intro.vase true):
            jump intro_home_vase
        "[Tidy up the desk]" if (!= $data.intro.desk true):
            run transition_fromStudy typewriter
            set data.intro.desk true
            "A typewriter, askew, almost falling off of the desk. Yours, probably."
            if (roll intro_home_menu_typewriter_orb orb 20):
                talk orb talk "An old model. It was used during the war for secretary work. Produced en masse and sold off cheap when the nation stopped needing to keep tabs on how many shells the factories were churning out in a day."
                talk orb talk "Or stopped being able to afford to pay someone to do that, at least."
                talk orb talk "The production line still rolls, but no one knows at what rate, or to what end. All that matters is that the boys in Noqui keep giving the factory a gangrenous thumbs up."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            "Aside the typewriter there are a few knocked over possessions. Empty medicinal packets, mostly."
            clear_dialog
            // if $data.intro.bloodCleaned:
            //     run transition intro_study
            // else:
            //     run transition intro_study_blood
            run transition_study true
            jump intro_home_menu
        "[Peer through the wrecked ceiling and out into the world]" if (!= $data.intro.peer true):
            run transition_fromStudy intro_hole_closeup
            set data.intro.peer true
            "Above you, the grey morning sky. Stars barely visible behind dark clouds."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "Home... will I ever return there..."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "FUCK. This is awful. How do I stop feeling sad..."
            clear_dialog
            "A raindrop lands directly on your eyeball. You flinch and make a gay little sound. It's grey out. Autumn is coming to a close. It will be a cold Winter."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk orb talk "All the more reason to fix up this roof. You'll catch your death of cold sleeping in here."
                "Brr!":
                    run skip
                "I'll be fine. I have a *very* strong immune system.":
                    if (roll intro_home_menu_immune_orb orb 40):
                        talk orb talk "No you don't. Get that hole fixed or you'll catch your death of cold."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            // if $data.intro.bloodCleaned:
            //     run transition intro_study
            // else:
            //     run transition intro_study_blood
            run transition_study true
            jump intro_home_menu
        "[Have a look at your bookcase]" if (!= $data.intro.bookcase true):
            set data.intro.bookcase true
            run transition_fromStudy intro_bookshelf
            "Your bookcase is a little sparse. A few titles stand out, some vague memory attached to them. <span class='writtenText'>'Blood in the Snow: The 1507 Azure War'</span>, <span class='writtenText'>'Manners for Girls'</span>, <span class='writtenText'>'You're the Hero: Swamp Bastards Revenge Gamebook'</span>, <span class='writtenText'>'Traumadoll'</span>, <span class='writtenText'>'Genevieve Lafonte's Beret Wearing Guidebook'</span> and <span class='writtenText'>'Seven Plants I Saw: An Adventure Story'</span>."
            clear_dialog
            "Strange. Only <span class='writtenText'>'Traumadoll'</span> and <span class='writtenText'>'Genevieve Lafonte's Beret Wearing Guidebook'</span> seem to hold any real sway in your heart these days. Both are in a noticeably newer condition than the others."
            clear_dialog
            "There are a few gramophone records. Alternative Bop, mostly. Shredded by wooden splinters and shards of rooftile and now completely pointless."
            run transition_study true
            jump intro_home_menu
        "So. That was a lot of work, the room still looks like a bomb went off, and it didn't even help me remember who I am." if (&& $data.intro.vase $data.intro.blood $data.intro.debris $data.intro.peer $data.intro.desk $data.intro.bookcase):
            run transition_fromStudy intro_ghost
            talk orb talk "Hmm. It didn't really did it. Sorry."
            start_quest intro
            choice:
                talk lovely talk "Mayhap one of your neighbours can shed some light on your identity? Shall we make our way outside?"
                "[Step outside into our Lovely Ladyverse] <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
                    play sound spendAction
                    stop ambient 1
                    jump goToGameMap

intro_home_debris:
    set data.intro.debris true
    run transition_study false
    "You tidy up the floor. It's frustrating and painful work, picking up all the splinters one at a time, but you manage it eventually, with only several small wounds to show for it."
    clear_dialog
    if (roll intro_home_dust_penny_orb orb 40):
        choice:
            talk orb talk "Check under the desk. There's more than just splinters hiding away there."
            "[Check under the desk]":
                "Hidden away under the desk are a few pennies. They're dusty and must have been down there for some time. None of them are legal tender in Anglia, though."
                if (roll intro_home_dust_dust_orb orb 40):
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "The cottage's previous owner spent a lot of time in Frankreich, and even more time dropping the coins they brought back onto the floor, apparently."
                        "[Pick them up]":
                            add_item pennies 1
                            play sound coins
                            talk lovely talk "Find a penny pick it up!"
                            talk nasty talk "Find a lady pick 'er up. Wahey!"
                            talk lovely talk "Scream!"
                            clear_dialog
                            talk orb talk "It's fun to find treasures... fun's new to me."
                        "Why did you bother getting me to find money I can't spend?":
                            talk orb talk "Because it's fun to find treasures? I don't know. I thought it would be fun. Fun's new to me, I was excited."
                else:
                    wait 1000
            "I'm good, thanks.":
                talk orb talk "Okay. There's literally no reason not to look, but whatever I guess, it's your cottage."
    else:
        wait 1000
    jump intro_home_menu

intro_home_vase:
    set data.intro.vase true
    choice:
        "You pick up the shards of the puzzle piece by piece and get to work. You are going to fix this vase. Or are you? It's pretty fucked. You aren't really supposed to fix vases when they're in a hundred bits, right? That's when you just call it a day and buy a new vase, isn't it?"
        roll intro_home_vase_vase_lovely lovely 90 "[Fix the broken vase]":
            success "":
                run transition_fromStudy intro_vase
                "You aren't sure how exactly, but your vase sits in front of you, as good as new, more or less."
                clear_dialog
                talk lovely talk "Wheee! We did it! With a delicate touch any true lovely lady can fix crockery, no matter how broken, without the need for something so working class as glue. This vase is held together with willpower and love alone!"
                talk orb talk "Even I can't explain this nonsense. Let's not look at it too long in case reality collapses."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    "It's too late. You're already looking. Reality hangs on the edge of a razor blade, but you don't care. The vase speaks to you. Sharp chunks of ceramic held together with naught but faith in their own vaseness."
                    "\\"How dare you be content enough with your lot in life that you can be held together with naught but your own damnable certainty!\\" [Smash the smug asshole]":
                        play sound vasesmash
                        animate #narrat-app narrat-screenshake
                        // if $data.intro.bloodCleaned:
                        //     run transition intro_study
                        // else:
                        //     run transition intro_study_blood
                        run transition_study true
                        set data.intro.smashedVase true
                        "The vase is once again shattered. A ceramic minefield now covers your bedroom floor. A field of skulls and broken teeth. Your enemy has been vanquished and its corpse despoiled."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk orb talk "Are you fucking kidding me? What a waste of all our time!"
                        clear_dialog
                        talk lovely talk "Oh really now, darling! What a mess you've made for the maid!"
                        talk lovely talk "Y- you do have a maid, don't you?"
                        talk orb talk "Does this place *look* like it has a maid?"
                        talk lovely talk "Tsk. Not to worry, I always keep a spare maid dress on me. Mayhap we can wrestle Nasty Girl into it?"
                        talk nasty talk "Fuck off / kill yourself etc."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk orb talk "I- I could wear the dress. I'd be so pretty..."
                        talk lovely talk "How adorable! I'll see if I can find it!"
                        talk orb talk "B- baka..."
                        jump intro_home_menu
                    "[Let it be]":
                        // if $data.intro.bloodCleaned:
                        //     run transition intro_study
                        // else:
                        //     run transition intro_study_blood
                        set data.intro.fixedVase true
                        run transition_study true
                        jump intro_home_menu
            failed "":
                run transition_study false
                "You press a shard of ceramic against another shard of ceramic. They do not stick together, obviously."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk orb talk "Really not sure what you expected, Ghost."
                    "[Try again]":
                        choice:
                            "The vase just doesn't seem to want to come back together. Its constituent parts sit there, mocking you. A shadow of its former self. Did you put it together in the wrong order? Are pieces missing? Was the vase ever assembled in the first place?"
                            "[Throw the pieces away]":
                                play sound vasetinkle
                                "The ceramic tinkles and echoes as it hits the metal base of the kitchen bin, like shards of ceramic falling into a metal bin."
                                jump intro_home_menu
        "[Throw the pieces away]":
            play sound vasetinkle
            run transition_study false
            "The ceramic tinkles and echoes as it hits the metal base of the kitchen bin, like shards of ceramic falling into a metal bin."
            jump intro_home_menu